{
  "_comment": [
    "Single source of inputs for the dual-stack wire-parity harness.",
    "Consumed by BOTH src/lib/transport.parity.test.ts (TS WebSerial dump)",
    "and tests/test_contract_dualstack_parity.py (backend capture + compare).",
    "Never let the two sides define their own inputs — that is how the",
    "hand-maintained expectations in transport.dispatch.test.ts and",
    "test_contract_pymavlink.py drifted apart in the first place.",
    "kind=dispatch drives transport.dispatch()/commands.execute() with op/param/data.",
    "Other kinds are choreographed flows implemented in code on both sides.",
    "expect: 'parity' = decoded frames must match field-by-field;",
    "        'both_drop' = both sides must emit zero frames;",
    "        'pinned_divergence' = behavior differs BY POLICY — pins today's",
    "        frame counts on each side so any change (fix or new drift)",
    "        resurfaces for an explicit decision. The 6 divergences found",
    "        when the harness was built (2026-07-14) were aligned to the",
    "        backend's validation policy the same day and are now both_drop;",
    "        the mechanism stays for whatever the harness finds next."
  ],
